    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-10T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1282b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-10T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 10, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Department’s 27, June 30, 5 p.m. The Department is still without any
                    information concerning Bolivian Government’s views as to how it can be helpful
                    in straightening out the matter. Please endeavor to obtain discreetly Bolivian
                    Government’s views as to a satisfactory settlement of the matter with a view to
                    reestablishing diplomatic relations. A similar inquiry is being made at Asunción
                    in order to see if there is anything the neutrals can do to be helpful in this
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
